JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 73
IS  - 2
SP  - 413
EP  - 436
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper models an agent in a three-period setting who does not update according to Bayes' Rule and who is self-aware and anticipates her updating behaviour when formulating plans. Gul and Pesendorfer's theory of temptation and self-control is a key building block. The main result is a representation theorem that generalizes (the dynamic version of) Anscombe-Aumann's theorem so that both the prior and the way in which it is updated are subjective. The model can accommodate updating biases analogous to those observed by psychologists.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00381.x
ER  - 



